RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Bellingham, WA operates under a strong-Mayor, weak-Council form of government. The Mayor is elected for a four-year term. The City Council consists of seven members; six are elected by wards for four-year terms, and one is elected at-large for a two-year term. The terms listed are based on the 2025 Council Member Contact List, which indicates terms ending in December 2025 or December 2027.
